content:
Debug your FlexCard's client and server-side actions and events with the Action Debugger in the FlexCard Designer's Preview tab. View requests and responses to see when and where errors occur to determine how to fix them.

View the configuration, status, and responses of parent and child data sources. View data source type and relevant settings, such as delay time from the config property. See if the data source successfully returns data in the status field. View the returned data in the response field.

View the response of each action or event executed on your FlexCard. Click an actionable item to display its debug log and associated events. Debug before publishing your FlexCard to a Salesforce page or third-party application.
title: Debugging FlexCards with Action Debugger in OmniStudio
